## Problem

`client/src/components/App.tsx` has no Error Boundary wrapping child components.

If any error occurs in:
- Keyboard event handling
- Mouse event handling
- Terminal rendering
- Action execution

The entire application crashes with no recovery option.

## Impact

- **User experience**: White screen on any runtime error
- **Debugging**: No error context shown to user
- **Recovery**: Must refresh page to recover

## Proposed Solution

Create `client/src/components/ErrorBoundary.tsx`:

```typescript
import { Component, type ComponentChildren } from 'preact';

interface Props {
  children: ComponentChildren;
  fallback?: (error: Error, reset: () => void) => ComponentChildren;
}

interface State {
  error: Error | null;
}

export class ErrorBoundary extends Component<Props, State> {
  state: State = { error: null };

  static getDerivedStateFromError(error: Error): State {
    return { error };
  }

  componentDidCatch(error: Error, errorInfo: any) {
    // Log to debug module
    debug.error('React error boundary caught:', error, errorInfo);
  }

  reset = () => {
    this.setState({ error: null });
  };

  render() {
    const { error } = this.state;
    const { children, fallback } = this.props;

    if (error) {
      if (fallback) {
        return fallback(error, this.reset);
      }

      return (
        <div class="error-boundary">
          <h2>Something went wrong</h2>
          <pre>{error.message}</pre>
          <button onClick={this.reset}>Try Again</button>
        </div>
      );
    }

    return children;
  }
}
```

**Usage in App.tsx:**
```typescript
import { ErrorBoundary } from './ErrorBoundary';

export function App() {
  return (
    <ErrorBoundary>
      <div class="app" data-theme={store.theme}>
        <WindowSwitcher />
        <TerminalGrid windowId={store.activeWindow} />
        {/* ... */}
      </div>
    </ErrorBoundary>
  );
}
```

## Granular Boundaries (Optional)

For better isolation, wrap individual panes:
```typescript
<ErrorBoundary fallback={(e) => <PaneError error={e} paneId={paneId} />}>
  <TerminalPane paneId={paneId} />
</ErrorBoundary>
```

This allows one pane to crash without affecting others.

