## Problem

`client/src/terminal/connection.ts` uses 11 separate callback properties (lines 136-146):

```typescript
public onSnapshot: ((snapshot: TerminalSnapshot) => void) | null = null;
public onDelta: ((delta: DeltaUpdate) => void) | null = null;
public onOutput: ((data: string) => void) | null = null;
public onTitle: ((paneId: number, title: string) => void) | null = null;
public onBell: (() => void) | null = null;
public onMasterChanged: ((masterId: string | null) => void) | null = null;
public onLayout: ((windowId: number, layout: WindowLayout) => void) | null = null;
public onLayoutList: ((templates: LayoutTemplate[]) => void) | null = null;
public onConnect: (() => void) | null = null;
public onDisconnect: (() => void) | null = null;
public onError: ((error: Error) => void) | null = null;
```

## Issues

1. **No multiple listeners**: Can only have one handler per event
2. **Manual null checks**: Every emit requires `this.onSnapshot?.(...)`
3. **Hard to debug**: Can't inspect registered listeners
4. **Violates observer pattern**: Standard pattern uses EventEmitter
5. **Verbose**: 11 public properties pollute the API surface

## Proposed Solution

Replace with typed EventEmitter pattern:

```typescript
type ConnectionEvents = {
  snapshot: (snapshot: TerminalSnapshot) => void;
  delta: (delta: DeltaUpdate) => void;
  output: (data: string) => void;
  title: (paneId: number, title: string) => void;
  bell: () => void;
  masterChanged: (masterId: string | null) => void;
  layout: (windowId: number, layout: WindowLayout) => void;
  layoutList: (templates: LayoutTemplate[]) => void;
  connect: () => void;
  disconnect: () => void;
  error: (error: Error) => void;
};

class TerminalConnection {
  private emitter = new TypedEventEmitter<ConnectionEvents>();

  on<K extends keyof ConnectionEvents>(event: K, callback: ConnectionEvents[K]): void {
    this.emitter.on(event, callback);
  }

  off<K extends keyof ConnectionEvents>(event: K, callback: ConnectionEvents[K]): void {
    this.emitter.off(event, callback);
  }

  private emit<K extends keyof ConnectionEvents>(
    event: K, 
    ...args: Parameters<ConnectionEvents[K]>
  ): void {
    this.emitter.emit(event, ...args);
  }
}
```

